{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b17ea630-ea58-4ac9-a70e-74e5a76f92ea","content":"Yes, both are correct for .NET MAUI on .NET 10.\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — This iOS platform-specific property adjusts page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island. Add the namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n    ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — This lets a specific layout (like a `Grid` with a background image) extend into the unsafe area, even when the page respects safe area insets:\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\nThese two complement each other: `UseSafeArea` keeps your interactive content clear of the notch, while `IgnoreSafeArea` on a background element lets it bleed edge-to-edge. Both APIs are stable and the recommended approach in .NET MAUI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c8ceba1-6342-4aef-a3e4-e00d1ed5e497","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid for background images\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling has evolved:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` - This is a platform-specific property from Xamarin.Forms that was carried over to .NET MAUI. In .NET MAUI, the correct way is `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"` and then `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`.\n\n\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea` is available on layouts in .NET MAUI, allowing views to extend beyond the safe area boundaries. For .NET 10, these APIs should still be the standard approach for handling safe area behavior on iOS. These are stable, well-established MAUI APIs, so I can answer directly based on what I know about them.","outputTokens":946,"requestId":"E83F:29C906:26B3C93:2AE791F:69F9439A"},"id":"056bd6b3-d168-46cb-801a-319f573578f6","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:11:08.607Z","parentId":"a69effd7-d9d1-4492-97da-93fe9cd7c016"}
